# IMF.P.Security.TestAccessViewer
# Purpose: Test that viewers cannot modify dimensions or view draft work versions unless explicitly permitted.
# Sources:
# - IMF security control model
# - IMF.C.Version ownership metadata where applicable
# - TM1 native security control objects where applicable
# Parameters:
# - pEnvironment: Parameter pEnvironment Default 'DEV'.
# - pLogToCube: Parameter pLogToCube Default 'Y'.
# - pLogFile: Parameter pLogFile Default 'docs/security/IMF_Security_Audit.log'.
# - pExpectedOutcome: Parameter pExpectedOutcome Default 'PASS'.
# Prolog:
# - Execute the process-specific security hardening workflow.
# Metadata:
# - No metadata datasource is required in this scaffold.
# Data:
# - No Data tab logic is implemented unless explicitly required later.
# Epilog:
# - Leave a deterministic log trail and clearly surface all TODOs.

#region prolog
sEnvironment = Upper(Trim(pEnvironment));
If(sEnvironment @= ''); sEnvironment = 'DEV'; EndIf;
ExecuteProcess('IMF.P.Security.LogSecurityEvent', 'pEnvironment', sEnvironment, 'pAction', 'TEST_ACCESS_VIEWER', 'pObjectType', 'REGRESSION', 'pObjectName', 'IMF_Viewer', 'pStatus', 'INFO', 'pMessage', 'Running viewer access regression test.', 'pLogToCube', pLogToCube, 'pLogFile', pLogFile);
# TODO: Execute a controlled viewer-session simulation in the target environment.
# TODO: Verify viewer cannot modify dimensions and cannot see draft work versions by default.
